Introduction
============

This is the Python bindings for SoftLayer Object Storage. Simple usage:

    import object_storage

    # Create a client instance
    client = object_storage.get_client('username', 'api_key')

    # Create a new container
    container = client['container'].create()

    # Create a new object
    obj = container['sample_object.txt'].create()

    # Upload plain text to the object storage.
    obj.send('Text')

    # Download object
    print obj.read()

    # Download object in chunks.
    for chunk in obj.iter_content(chunk_size=2):
        print "Read:", chunk

    # List objects in container
    for o in container:
        print o.name
    # or
    print container.list()

    # Delete object
    obj.delete()

    # Delete container
    container.delete()
